<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id2e8e93bf-3a70-11f1-8334-895c8eef5d79" identifier="/us/usc/t23/s301"><num value="301">§ 301.</num><heading> Freedom from tolls</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Except as provided in <ref href="/us/usc/t23/s129">section 129 of this title</ref> with respect to certain toll bridges and toll tunnels, all highways constructed under the provisions of this title shall be free from tolls of all kinds.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id2e8e93c0-3a70-11f1-8334-895c8eef5d79">(<ref href="/us/pl/85/767">Pub. L. 85–767</ref>, <date date="1958-08-27">Aug. 27, 1958</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/72/912">72 Stat. 912</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
